{
  "texts": [
    "A confusion matrix is a table that visualizes the performance of a classifier.",
    "The main diagonal value is the number of PSE reports that have been classified as true event types, whereas off-diagonal values are the number of PSE reports that have been wrongly classified.",
    "While the classifier was able to classify the majority of event types of PSE reports correctly, there is a consistent misclassification of the omission or errors in assessment, diagnosis, or monitoring PSE report as the care coordination or communication (coordination) event type.",
    "LIME-Based Explainability AnalysisWe used LIME to evaluate whether the SVM classifier trained with RoBERTa-base has leveraged informative words for classification.",
    "Figure 2 presents 3 examples of explanations for the classifier's predictions."
